<LanguageData>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.0>questDescription(asker_factionLeader==True)->[asker_nameDef], [asker_faction_leaderTitle] of [asker_faction_name], has informed us of the location of a sealed entrance to one of the [uraltSilos] left behind during Operation: Deadlife, a planet-spanning initiative launched by a [longDeadGovernment] in preparation for global catastrophe.\n\nThese silos were designed to remain sealed for generations, [intention]. Inside, it's believed they contain [containedReward]. The deeper chambers are rumored to halt equipment and supplies capable of restarting civilization itself.\n\n[threat]. [importantLight]. Without the light, you’ll be navigating blind and vulnerable to attack.\n\n[commandMap]. Studying these might reveal the locations of other silos, and more importantly, bring us closer to discovering the Command Headquarters, the nerve center of Operation: Deadlife, where the truth behind this apocalyptic plan may still lie buried.\n\n[questObjective].</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.0>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.1>questDescription(askerIsNull==True)->The alt battle maps have revealed to us the location of a sealed entrance to one of the [uraltSilos] left behind during Operation: Deadlife, a planet-spanning initiative launched by a [longDeadGovernment] in preparation for global catastrophe.\n\nThese silos were designed to remain sealed for generations, [intention]. Inside, it's believed they contain [containedReward]. The deeper chambers are rumored to halt equipment and supplies capable of restarting civilization itself.\n\n[threat]. [importantLight]. Without the light, you’ll be navigating blind and vulnerable to attack.\n\n[commandMap]. Studying these might reveal the locations of other silos, and more importantly, bring us closer to discovering the Command Headquarters, the nerve center of Operation: Deadlife, where the truth behind this apocalyptic plan may still lie buried.\n\n[questObjective].</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.1>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.10>uraltSilos->deadlife supply silos</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.10>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.11>longDeadGovernment->long-dead government</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.11>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.12>longDeadGovernment->uralt planetary alliance</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.12>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.13>longDeadGovernment->collapsed technocratic regime</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.13>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.14>longDeadGovernment->extinct militarized government</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.14>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.15>longDeadGovernment->forgotten emergency council</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.15>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.16>longDeadGovernment->defunct crisis-state authority</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.16>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.17>longDeadGovernment->long-vanished defense network</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.17>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.18>longDeadGovernment->fallen civil defense command</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.18>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.19>intention->intended to be opened only when humanity faced collapse</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.19>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.2>uraltSilos->uralt military silos</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.2>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.20>intention->built to withstand centuries and reopen in humanity’s darkest hour</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.20>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.21>intention->designed as failsafe supply nodes for rebuilding civilization</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.21>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.22>intention->meant to be activated only during a planetary extinction event</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.22>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.23>intention->set to unlock once the collapse protocols were confirmed</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.23>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.24>intention->intended to serve as last-resort caches for surviving factions</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.24>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.25>containedReward->vast stockpiles of resources: steel, plasteel, medicine, weaponry, and even preserved cultural relics</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.25>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.26>containedReward->a wealth of resources: hardened rations, components, medical supplies, and munitions</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.26>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.27>containedReward->critical survival materials: building materials, medicines, weapons, and schematics</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.27>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.28>containedReward->tools to rebuild: fuel, tools, seeds, weapons, and encrypted blueprints</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.28>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.29>containedReward->enough equipment to sustain or restart a new colony</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.29>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.3>uraltSilos->sealed war-era bunkers</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.3>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.30>containedReward->a treasure trove of essential gear, preserved through time</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.30>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.31>threat->Yet the silos are not empty. The corridors within are completely lightless, and something hostile is said to lurk in the dark</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.31>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.32>threat->But time has not left them untouched. The interior is pitch black, and something stirs in the shadows</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.32>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.33>threat->Explorers report movement inside: faint noises, heavy footsteps, shapes in the dark</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.33>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.34>threat->Survivors speak of hostile entities lurking in the corridors, unseen until it’s too late</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.34>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.35>threat->Whatever remains inside is not dormant, something guards these forgotten halls</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.35>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.36>threat->The halls are quiet, but not empty. Something waits inside, cloaked in shadow</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.36>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.37>importantLight->Activating the power and lighting systems inside is critical</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.37>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.38>importantLight->Restoring power and activating lights will be vital to survival</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.38>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.39>importantLight->Without illumination, any movement inside the silo is suicide</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.39>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.4>uraltSilos->abandoned military silos</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.4>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.40>importantLight->Light systems must be activated first, or you’ll be helpless in the dark</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.40>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.41>importantLight->Sight is your only defense. Find a way to power the lights quickly</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.41>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.42>importantLight->Unless you activate the lights, the silo will be a deathtrap</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.42>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.43>commandMap->Each silo is also known to contain at least one uralt command desk or map table used to coordinate military movements</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.43>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.44>commandMap->Most silos house uralt desks or battle maps once used by field commanders</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.44>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.45>commandMap->Tactical tables scattered inside may contain encrypted maps to other installations</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.45>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.46>commandMap->Buried among the supplies are command desks filled with strategic data</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.46>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.47>commandMap->Decoding the maps on-site could reveal new locations tied to Operation: Deadlife</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.47>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.48>commandMap->Intact terminals and war tables could lead us to the central command</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.48>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.49>questObjective->The quest will complete once you loot at least a quarter of resources from the silo</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.49>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.5>uraltSilos->pre-collapse resource vaults</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.5>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.50>questObjective->Loot at least 25% of the total resources stored in the silo to complete the quest</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.50>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.51>questObjective->The mission ends once a significant portion of the stored goods have been secured</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.51>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.52>questObjective->Successfully extracting a quarter of the silo’s contents will fulfill the objective</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.52>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.53>questObjective->You’ll need to claim at least a fourth of the silo’s supplies to mark this operation complete</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.53>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.54>questObjective->Once enough materials have been secured and hauled out, the quest will be marked complete</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.54>
